olive oil
1 packet Jasmine rice
1 Carrot
1 cob Corn
½ Lemon
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet Southeast Asian Spice Blend
2.5 tbs plain flour
¼ tsp salt
1 packet Diced Chicken
2 packet soy sauce mix
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet coriander

• Boil the kettle.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water. Add jasmine rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12-14 minutes.
• Drain, rinse with warm water and set aside. Cover to keep warm.

• Thinly slice carrot into half-moons. Slice kernels off the corn cob. Cut lemon into wedges.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook carrot and corn kernels until lightly browned,
4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer to a large bowl.

• In a medium bowl, combine Southeast Asian spice blend, the plain flour and salt. Add diced chicken and toss to coat.
• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to medium-high heat with enough olive oil to cover the base. When oil is hot, pick up chicken using tongs and shake off any excess flour. Cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• To the bowl of veggies, add cooked rice, soy sauce mix and a squeeze of lemon juice. Stir to combine.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it’s no longer pink inside.

• Divide veggie fried rice between bowls. Top with salt-pepper chicken and drizzle with garlic aioli.
• Tear over coriander and serve with remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch and tear over the coriander!